"Oil and gas agreements form the backbone of this alliance. I propose we work further towards establishing energy independence."

Narrator

I saw nods of agreement around the table.

Player_Romus

"Therefore, I pledge to fund our alliance on an ongoing basis."

"Therefore, I pledge that I will fund our alliance on an ongoing basis." [-3 Budget Per Turn]

Player_Romus

"I shall contribute a generous sum towards the founding of a joint financial reserve."

"I shall contribute a generous sum towards the founding of a joint financial reserve." [-5 Budget]

Player_Romus

"Rizia itself will not commit any finances, but my councilors are prepared to aid in the across-the-board coordination of our fiscal policies."

Axel Reinhart

"I liked this idea in theory. But the vagueness of it all concerns me greatly."

Laurento Esquibel

"Your reservations are completely understandable. Which is why we have dedicated a portion of this meeting to go through each of your individual concerns."

Laurento Esquibel

"I'm pleased to hear you're all happy with our suggestions."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"I was more than satisfied with the outcome of our Zille negotiations. However, I have not yet had the chance to build such a foundation of trust with our neighbors here."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"We're talking about oil. Not gas."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"This is my condition, Your Majesty. I believe the others will find it reasonable."

Narrator

Smolak and Reinhart both appeared satisfied.

Axel Reinhart

"I can live with that."

Player_Romus

"You're going to regret this, Smolak."

Player_Romus

"How is little Wiktor II these days?"

Jorga Azmal

"I agree to everything. The Lord has truly smiled upon us this day, Your Majesty."

Player_Romus

"The Lord says no. I cannot help you with this."

Laurento Esquibel

"Perhaps leaving Derdia out of this alliance will be better for our image in the long run."

Axel Reinhart

"But I do have concerns."

Axel Reinhart

"But your Intermerkopum plan includes no such conditions."

Player_Romus

"You trounced us in the 1920s, and now you're begging us for military support? How the tables have turned."

RiziaDLC.Vina_MarriageDecision_Axel == true && RiziaDLC.Vina_KeepsLastName == true && RiziaDLC.Vina_Escapes == false

nan

Axel Reinhart

"The name's Toras, remember? I gave up my entire heritage for your kingdom."

Player_Romus

"We can commit troops for the purpose of deterring potential aggressors."

"We can commit troops for the purpose of deterring potential aggressors." [-500 Manpower]

Player_Romus

"We will earmark a stockpile of military equipment specifically for the defense of Pales."

"We will earmark a stockpile of military equipment specifically for the defense of Pales." [-1000 Equipment]

Player_Romus

"We can't commit any military resources, but we will earmark treasury funds for the purpose of Palesian defense."

"We can't commit any military resources, but we will earmark treasury funds for the purpose of Palesian defense." [-1 Budget]

Player_Romus

"Too bad for you. We will not grant you any special favors."

Axel Reinhart

"Good luck to the rest of you."

Narrator

Laurento cautiously looked around the chamber.

Axel Reinhart

"I signed up for this union. I'm in it for the long haul, no matter what."

Player_Romus

"Excellent. I knew you wouldn't let me down."

Narrator

She took a long glance around the table.

Player_Romus

"You don't have to like the others. This is a practical agreement, pure and simple."

Alma Saltana

"I know that the Rizian government responded disproportionately."

Axel Reinhart

"You know how much damage revolutionaries have done in your country and mine. Surely you won't give in to this request."

Player_Romus

"I am sorry, Ms. Saltana, but I cannot do as you ask."

Narrator

She stood up and pushed in her chair.

Narrator

Laurento waited until she had left to speak.

Jorga Azmal

"It's just you, me and the Lord now, Your Majesty."

Alma Saltana

"And then there were two."

Axel Reinhart

"That's what your grand alliance plans have come to? Two countries that are stuck together anyway?"

Player_Romus

"Thank you for believing in this project. Even if no one else did."

Player_Romus

"I'm sorry for wasting your time."

Player_Romus

"No matter what, I am proud to call Derdia an ally."

Player_Romus

"Thank you for believing in this project. Even if no one else did."

Player_Romus

"I'm sorry for wasting your time."

Player_Romus

"No matter what, I am proud to have Pales on our side after all these years."

Wiktor Smolak (R)

"Not at all. I'll take any excuse to visit my favorite neighbor."

Jorga Azmal

"If we do not have faith, what do we have?"

Jorga Azmal

"Time spent in Rizia is not a waste. I'll make my way to Plavo while I'm here."

Narrator

I hoped that my kingdom would not do the same.

Laurento Esquibel

"That's it, then. We have an alliance."

Player_Romus

"I can't wait to rub this in my sister-in-law's face. Regally, of course."

Alma Saltana

"Thank you once more for all of your efforts, {RiziaDLCText.SaltanaToPlayer}."

Jorga Azmal

"We are uniting the ancestral lands of St. Wruhec. Just as the Lord has prophesied."

Axel Reinhart

"Nice one, Your Majesty. We'll celebrate over dinner soon."

Narrator

I slowly walked to the head of the table and picked up the pen.

Narrator

Now all I had to do was tell Queen Beatrice.

Narrator

My tablemates looked at me in trepidation.

Player_Romus

"War is in the air, my friends. It will come to all of us sooner or later."

Player_Romus

"Once we defeat Pales, I will be able to pledge vast amounts of military equipment towards a common Intermerkopum stockpile."
